<p><a href="http://www.popsci.com/announcements/article/2012-04/may-2012-new-age-flight"><img src="http://www.popsci.com/files/maycoverside.jpg" style="float: left; margin-top: 0.5em;" /></a><br />
<div style="float: right; margin-top: -1.5em; align: right; width: 190px">
<h3 style="line-height: 1.2em;"><a href="http://www.popsci.com/announcements/article/2012-04/may-2012-new-age-flight">May 2012: The New Age of Flight</a></h3>
<p>Our 140th anniversary issue takes a look at the future of flight, from super-quiet supersonic jets to the first personal electric plane to, yes, a clip-out (or print-out) paper airplane.</p>
<p>Plus: China's green-aviation experiment, the case for human pilots over drones, and a curious mystery, 140 years in the making.</p>
